  "title": "Manager, Communications & Partnerships (North, up to $5,000)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Lead the organization’s content strategy, delivering clear, compelling messaging supported by data insights, storytelling, and high-quality visual assets.</li>\n  <li>Design and implement communications strategies that support fundraising goals an deepen donor relationships.</li>\n  <li>Cultivate and manage relationships with key media outlets and partners to enhance visibility and credibility.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Marketing or equivalent</li>\n  <li>At least 3 years of experience in <strong>strategic communications, branding, or public relations preferably within the non-profit, social service, or community development </strong>sector.</li>\n  <li>Strategic thinker with the ability to balance high-level planning with hands-on execution.</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal and stakeholder management skills, including cross-functional collaboration.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
